Gill expressed his honor in leading alongside legends Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma, drawing inspiration from their careers and valuing their experience as he aims to build on the team's legacy.
title: Shubman Gill reveals behind-the-scenes moments with Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: A 42-year-old constable, E Pramod, was fatally stabbed by a habitual offender in Nizamabad city while being transported to a police station. The accused, involved in chain snatching and theft, attacked Pramod with a knife on his chest before fleeing. Police have launched a search operation and registered a murder case.
title: Telangana: Man stabs cop to death while being taken to police station

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: ICE agents kicked down a door and pointed guns at a mother holding her infant during a raid in Portland, Oregon. The family claims the detained men entered legally, while a DHS official stated the operation targeted a previously removed violent criminal. The main suspect remains at large.
title: Watch: ICE agents barge into Portland family's home; point gun at them as baby cries

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Jyothi Surekha Vennam made history as the first Indian woman compound archer to win a medal at the World Cup Final, securing bronze in Nanjing. She achieved this by defeating world No. 2 Ella Gibson with a perfect performance, shooting 15 consecutive 10s. This marks a significant achievement for Vennam in her World Cup Final journey.
title: Bronze for India! Jyothi Vennam creates history at World Archery Final

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: A viral video shows the difficulties of walking on Indian footpaths. Content creator Caleb Friesen struggled with a baby stroller in Bengaluru, encountering numerous obstructions. His post humorously ranked these obstacles, placing pedestrians last. The video has sparked conversations about footpath accessibility across Indian cities. Friesen aims to raise awareness about these issues.
title: Canadian man highlights India’s footpath conditions - video goes viral

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A prominent Italian journalist, Sigfrido Ranucci, narrowly escaped a bomb attack on his car, which exploded near his home in Pomezia. His daughter had left the scene just 20 minutes prior. The blast caused significant damage but no injuries. Ranucci, who has been living under police protection due to mafia threats, received strong condemnation from Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni and other government officials.
title: Car bomb explodes in Italy: Anti-mafia journalist targeted

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Four police officers were injured outside the US embassy in Bogota, Colombia, after protesters launched arrows and explosives. The demonstration, organized by "Congreso de los Pueblos," aimed to oppose US policies and assert Colombian sovereignty. President Petro urged caution, noting a radical faction attacked police.
title: Colombia: Anti-Trump protesters fire arrows at police outside US embassy

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Diwali 2025 brings a series of state-specific bank holidays, with most branches remaining open nationwide on Dhanteras, except in Assam. Several states will observe closures from October 20th to 23rd for various Diwali-related festivals. Online banking and ATMs will remain accessible during these closures.
title: Diwali bank holidays: Are banks closed for 3 days this weekend? See state-wise list

author: MAHENDRA YADAV
description: Gold and silver prices are near record highs, presenting investors with a dilemma. Experts advise caution due to potential headwinds like easing geopolitical tensions and changing rate cut expectations. Investors are encouraged to hedge, book profits, or wait for dips before entering the market.
title: Gold & silver outlook: Will precious metals glitter or lose shine? Here's what experts say

author: TNN
description: On Saturday morning, a fire erupted in one of the AC coaches of the Amritsar-Saharsa Garib Rath Express near Sirhind. Thankfully, all passengers were promptly evacuated from the stricken compartment, and fortunately, there were no injuries reported. Railway officials responded swiftly to the incident, ensuring the safety of all travelers as they worked to contain the situation.
title: Punjab: Fire breaks out in AC coach of Amritsar-Saharsa Garib Rath Express; one injured

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: In a dramatic twist, Assam Police apprehended Md Injamul Hoque for creating a contentious video surrounding the death of popular singer Zubeen Garg in Singapore. Although authorities in Singapore are treating the case as an accidental drowning, Hoque admitted to manipulating and publishing provocative statements.
title: Zubeen Garg death probe: Assam Police nab man for posting controversial video

author: MAHESH BUDDI
description: Telugu Desam Party MLA Putta Sudhakar Yadav lost ₹1.07 crore to cybercriminals impersonating Mumbai cyber crime officials. The fraudsters threatened him with arrest in a fabricated money laundering and human trafficking case, demanding money for 'provisional bail'. The MLA reported the incident after realizing he was duped.
title: MLA Putta Sudhakar Yadav conned by fake Mumbai cops; loses Rs 1.07 crore

author: RAHUL SINGH
description: After enduring 11 years of wrongful imprisonment for a murder he did not commit, a farmer's long fight for justice has finally paid off. Misfortune and poverty had deprived him of legal aid, leaving him in a nightmarish limbo for over three decades.
title: 60-year-old UP man who couldn’t afford lawyer walks out of jail after 11 years

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Three masked individuals, dressed as Michael Myers, a clown, and a nun, terrorized a widow's home in Alexandria, Virginia, on Halloween night.  The intruders threatened to kill the occupants and attempted to break in, forcing the family to fear for their safety. Police are investigating the serious incident, which is being compared to 'The Purge'.
title: Halloween horror in Virginia: Masked trio tries to break into home - video

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi and other dignitaries on Saturday extended heartfelt Dhanteras greetings to citizens, praying for happiness, prosperity, and good health. Leaders emphasised the significance of the festival, linking it to wealth, health, and the birth anniversary of Lord Dhanvantari, while also urging for environmental protection and social harmony.
title: 'I pray for everyone's happiness, prosperity & health': PM wishes nation on Dhanteras

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Indian cricket titans Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma are poised to etch their names further in history during the upcoming ODI series against Australia. Kohli is on the cusp of becoming the second-highest ODI run-scorer, while Rohit eyes his 500th international cap and a record for most ODI sixes.
title: Ind vs Aus: Virat Kohli, Rohit Sharma set to smash multiple records in Australia

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Suryakumar Yadav, fresh off leading India to the Asia Cup title, revealed his past aspirations for ODI captaincy. He believes a stronger ODI performance could have opened doors, and despite Shubman Gill now leading in ODIs, Surya hasn't entirely given up on the dream. He's set to captain India in an upcoming T20I series against Australia.
title: 'ODI captaincy bhi mil sakti thi mujhe': Suryakumar spills the beans on ambition

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: Pishchane, Tykhe and ... : Russia claims to have captured 3 Ukrainian villages

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: China and the US are set to resume trade talks soon, aiming to de-escalate escalating tariff tensions. This comes after US President Trump suggested a 100% tariff might not be sustainable, while also hinting at potential further levies. The discussions follow recent export controls by Beijing and mixed signals from both economic powers.
title: Trump's 100% tariff: US and China seek fresh trade talks 'as soon as possible'

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Nvidia's advanced AI chip dominance in China has evaporated, dropping to zero due to US export controls. CEO Jensen Huang revealed the company is completely barred from selling high-performance chips, warning this exclusion harms both nations and cedes the market to domestic rivals like Huawei.  China's push for self-sufficiency accelerates this shift.
title: Upset Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang says: Our market share has fallen to Zero from 95% in ...

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The UN warns that ending the Gaza famine requires time and opening all crossings to flood the region with food. Nearly 3,000 tonnes of food have arrived since a ceasefire, with the World Food Programme scaling up aid.  More distribution points and bakeries are planned, but urgent calls persist for unimpeded access to save lives.
title: 'Will take time': UN issues warning on Gaza famine; urges opening of crossings

author: BARSHA DUTTA
description: A viral rumor claiming Adam Sandler would perform at Turning Point USA's halftime show has been debunked.  Misleading social media posts, amplified by manipulated graphics, falsely linked the comedian to Lara Trump's event.  Sources confirm Sandler remains focused on his comedy and film projects, with no political ties to the organization.
title: Adam Sandler won’t join Turning Point USA’s Super Bowl event

author: TNN
description: A 21-year-old engineering student was arrested and suspended for allegedly raping his senior in a college washroom. The survivor filed a complaint five days after the October 10 incident, leading to the accused's arrest and judicial custody. College authorities confirmed forming a committee to inquire into the matter.
title: Bengaluru college rape: Accused student had offered to bring pill

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Dhanteras, marking the start of Diwali, is dedicated to Goddess Lakshmi and Lord Dhanvantri, symbolizing divine blessings, wealth, and health. The article offers 75 messages, quotes, and wishes to share with loved ones, colleagues, and friends, emphasizing the importance of extending warm greetings and heartfelt gratitude during this auspicious occasion.
title: Happy Dhanteras 2025: 80 best wishes, messages and quotes to share with loved ones

title: Mozambique boat tragedy: Three Indians dead, five missing

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Three Afghan cricketers, Kabeer, Sibghatullah, and Haroon, were tragically killed in an attack in Paktika province. The Afghanistan Cricket Board blamed the "Pakistani regime" for the "cowardly attack." In response, Afghanistan has withdrawn from an upcoming T20I series against Pakistan. Captain Rashid Khan condemned the incident, calling it "immoral and barbaric."
title: Names and pictures of 3 Afghanistan cricketers killed in Paktika

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Afghanistan has withdrawn from a tri-nation series with Pakistan and Sri Lanka after three local cricketers were killed in an attack. The Afghanistan Cricket Board identified the victims and stated the attack was carried out by the Pakistani regime. The decision to withdraw is a gesture of respect to the victims.
title: Three Afghan cricketers killed in attack on Pak border; Rashid Khan breaks down

title: All not settled: Shah says NDA to fight Bihar polls under Nitish, but leaves CM decision to MLAs

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Teenage sensation Vaibhav Suryavanshi continues to captivate cricket fans, drawing massive crowds wherever he plays. Despite a modest score in Bihar's recent Ranji Trophy win, the 14-year-old prodigy, who also holds an IPL contract and an IPL century record, acknowledged his adoring supporters. Bihar is banking on his talent for a comeback.
title: 'Jiya ho bihar ke lala': Vaibhav Suryavanshi's gesture to fans in Patna wins hearts—Watch

author: DHANANJAY MAHAPATRA
title: Mancha Masjid case: SC rejects 400-yr-old mosque's plea against demolition; cites public interest

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: BCCI chief selector Ajit Agarkar addressed Mohammed Shami's criticism regarding his exclusion from the Australia white-ball tour. Agarkar stated that Shami's fitness was the primary concern, citing his inability to participate in the England tour. He emphasised that Shami's availability for the Ranji Trophy would be monitored, and if fit, he remains a valuable asset.
title: 'Might give him a call': Ajit Agarkar breaks silence on Md Shami controversy; what he said

author: NIKITA PATNAIK
description: NFL star Justin Herbert and pop sensation Madison Beer are the talk of 2025. Their romance, sparked by sightings and confirmed with a sideline kiss at a Chargers game, blends sports and entertainment. Beer's evolving style, from glamorous stage wear to chic off-duty looks, further fuels fan fascination with this high-profile couple.
title: Justin Herbert and Madison Beer: 2025’s hottest new couple stuns fans

author: MANOJ CHAURASIA
description: INDIA bloc partners faced a seat-sharing deadlock as nominations closed for the first phase of elections. Despite the impasse, candidates filed papers, with eight seats seeing friendly fights. VIP founder Mukesh Sahani opted out of contesting to focus on campaigning for the alliance's victory and a potential deputy CM role.
title: Bihar polls: 8 INDIA bloc allies risk friendly fights as multiple candidates stay in fray
